# UI Color Palette Preference

## Overview

Prefer non-purple as the primary UI color. Use purple only as a secondary/accent unless brand constraints require otherwise.

## Palette Priorities

- Primary (preferred): blue, teal, cyan, green, neutral/gray
- Secondary: orange, amber, slate
- Accent-only (low priority): purple, violet, fuchsia

## Common Patterns

```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #0ea5e9;   /* blue-500 */
  --color-secondary: #a855f7; /* violet-500 accent */
}
```

```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #8b5cf6; /* avoid: purple as primary */
}
```

```tsx
<button className="bg-sky-600 hover:bg-sky-700 text-white">Action</button>
```

```tsx
<button className="bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white">Action</button>
```

## Additional Guidelines

- Do not set purple as default brand color or primary theme token.
- Purple can be used for highlights, badges, or low-emphasis accents.
- Prefer accessible contrast (WCAG AA minimum for text and controls).
- If brand guidelines mandate purple primary, note that exception explicitly.
